<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Environmentalists are gearing up for an international `` Earth Day 1990'' that they hope will dwarf the original of 20 years ago, an event that helped make <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> laws more sensitive to environmental concerns. `` The purpose of Earth Day in 1970 was to organize a nationwide grassroots demonstration of public concern for the environment,'' former Sen. <PERSON> Gaylord </PERSON> <PERSON> Nelson </PERSON>, who founded the event, said Tuesday. `` Though much has been achieved in many areas in the past 20 years, we continue to lose ground in the fight to improve our environment.'' <PERSON> Denis </PERSON> <PERSON> Hayes </PERSON>, coordinator of the first Earth Day, and Sen. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Kerry </PERSON>, D-Mass. and Rep. <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Green </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-N </LOCATION>. Y, who were local Earth Day activists 20 years ago, joined <PERSON> Nelson </PERSON> at a news conference to announce plans for the April 22, 1990, <PERSON> Nelson </PERSON>, who now is counselor to the <ORGANIZATION> Wilderness </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION>, called on President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> to lead other heads of state into a `` battle to save the Earth.'' <PERSON> Hayes </PERSON> said the observance is meant to start a decade of environmental concern showing that countries throughout the world have a `` shared set of values and commitment to save the planet.'' He said that organizers have talked to members of the White House staff, but have not yet approached <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> directly. <PERSON> Nelson </PERSON> said no president campaigns against environmental policies, but none since <PERSON> Theodore </PERSON> <PERSON> Roosevelt </PERSON> has understood what needs to be done. Leaders of other nations have been similarly shortsighted, he said. `` In the leading industrial nations Prime Minister <PERSON> Thatcher </PERSON> and President <PERSON> Mitterand </PERSON> have joined President <PERS