criticizing the speaker's ethics while the case is still undecided But the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> is hoping <PERSON> Wright </PERSON>'s troubles make the public more receptive to its message that it is time to make Republicans the majority party for the first time since President <PERSON> Eisenhower </PERSON>'s first term House Minority Leader <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Michel </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-Ill </LOCATION>., and Rep. <PERSON> Mickey </PERSON> <PERSON> Edwards </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-Okla </LOCATION>., held a news conference Tuesday to announce their party's agenda and complain about the pace of legislation this `` It's time for Democrats to help govern or get out of the way,'' <PERSON> Edwards </PERSON> said.
