id. `` They ca n't say it's not connected, so they speculate that it is. But we have no evidence that it is connected to <LOCATION> Lockerbie </LOCATION> _ only the theoretic possibility exists.'' Police arrested 14 suspects in the October raids but only two, <PERSON> Hafez </PERSON> <PERSON> Kassem </PERSON> <PERSON> Dalkamoni </PERSON> and <PERSON> Abdul </PERSON> <PERSON> Fattah </PERSON> <PERSON> Ghandanfar </PERSON>, remain in custody. <PERSON> Prechtel </PERSON> said authorities expected to file charges against the two within a few months. They are suspected of forming terrorist cells in <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, illegal possession of weapons and bomb attacks on <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military trains in August 1987 and April 1988, <PERSON> Prechtel </PERSON> said.
