sed sessions, which start next week after four days of opening speeches by delegation chiefs. `` Our objective is not to be confrontational,'' said Marks. `` We want to try to solve problems ... we do n't need any more -LRB- agreements on -RRB- principles, we need action.'' The <LOCATION> Vienna </LOCATION> agreement was the outcome of East-West talks on human rights and free speech that began in <LOCATION> Helsinki </LOCATION> in the 1970s.
