from New York. Pick up 9th pvs, `Operation Lifeline...'</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DIDRIKKE SCHANCHE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Attackers ambushed and shot up the first truck convoy of a <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> famine relief effort intended to save 100,000 lives in the southern <LOCATION> Sudan </LOCATION> war zone, killing seven armed escorts, <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> officials said Wednesday. They said a civilian driver and two assistants were wounded, and radio reports from the scene identified the slain escorts as members of the rebel <ORGANIZATION> Sudan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> officials in <LOCATION> Nairobi </LOCATION> did not affix blame for the attack on the 14-truck convoy, but speculation centered on nomadic tribal warriors, army soldiers or government-sponsored militias operating against the rebels. The attack occurred Tuesday about 20 miles west of <LOCATION> Kapoeta </LOCATION>, a rebel base in southeastern <LOCATION> Sudan </LOCATION>, 50 miles north of the <LOCATION> Kenya </LOCATION> border. It was another setback for Operation Lifeline-Sudan, the $ 132 million <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> relief program plagued by delays caused by bureaucracy, bad weather and equipment shortages. Relief officials said the trucks were carrying 100 tons of food, medicine and other supplies to <LOCATION> Torit </LOCATION>, 100 miles west of <LOCATION> Kapoeta </LOCATION>, when they were halted by rocket and automatic weapons fire. It was the first convoy to <LOCATION> Torit </LOCATION> under the U.N.-sponsored effort to stockpile more than 100,000 tons of supplies in southern <LOCATION> Sudan </LOCATION> before heavy rains beginning next month make transport virtually impossible. Even before the attack, <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> officials had conceded they probably could not meet their goals before the rainy season, which lasts until November. `` We think it is an isolated incid