<HEAD>No Decision On Missiles</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RITA BEAMISH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> told a group of congressional leaders Wednesday that he has n't decision on future development of the MX nuclear missile, the legislators said. `` He's indicated he's working on the MX issue and he's anxious to receive the input from a wide variety of individuals on <LOCATION> Capitol </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hill </LOCATION>,'' said Sen. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Warner </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-Va </LOCATION>. `` He did not in any way strike a note of finality. <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> and other legislators said they did n't know whether <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> would support building a mobile version of the MX, would back the smaller Midgetman missile, or some combination of the two. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> discussed the issue with <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> members of both parties. He convened the group, along with his top foreign policy advisers, in what he intends to use as an occasional chance to consult with them on general foreign policy, his staff said. The missile question is part of an effort to build new weapons for the land-based leg of the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> nuclear arsenal. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s options are to base new 10-warhead MX missiles on rail cars, a system favored by <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> generals, or develop a new single-warhead missile known as the Midgetman, to be housed on trucks. The Midgetman is far more costly, with a price tag of nearly $ 24 billion for 500 single-warhead missiles, compared to $ 5.4 billion for the same capability on the multi-warhead MX, according to <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> estimates. The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> currently has 50 MX missiles based in silos in <LOCATION> Wyoming </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Nebraska </LOCATION>, in addition to the multi-warhead Minuteman missi