<HEAD>Frequent Flier Who Intervened In Eastern Case Wants Airline Back</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CAROLYN S. CARLSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Even if the strike against <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> is never resolved, <PERSON> Moreton </PERSON> <PERSON> Rolleston </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> figures his pilot son and flight attendant daughter-in-law eventually will find work. But he's worried about the effect on competition at <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>'s airport. The 71-year-old <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> lawyer said Tuesday he intervened in <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s bankruptcy case because he wants to make sure the idled airline returns to operation. `` This is real important to <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>,'' <PERSON> Rolleston </PERSON> said in an interview. `` Eastern had been running 100,000 people to <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> every day, 290 flights a day. Forty percent of the traffic in <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> was Eastern.'' <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Bankruptcy Judge <PERSON> Burton </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Lifland </PERSON> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> scheduled a hearing for next week on <PERSON> Rolleston </PERSON>'s motion to have the court to appoint a trustee to run <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> until parent <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> can sell it. <PERSON> Rolleston </PERSON> was allowed to intervene in the case because he is a member of <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s frequent flier program, which is run jointly with sister carrier <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>. Since he has mileage credits in the program, which rewards frequent fliers with free trips, the court considered him an Eastern creditor. Eastern spokeswoman <PERSON> Karen </PERSON> <PERSON> Ceremsak </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>'s current position is that <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATI