million a year ago. Revenues from market-making and principal transactions fell 9.6 percent to $ 319 million from $ 353 million in the 1988 quarter. The firm also showed a 71.2 percent drop in net interest income, to $ 19 million from $ 66 million a year ago, blaming a rise in short-term rates that have often outpaced long-term ones. <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> owns a controlling stake in <LOCATION> Shearson </LOCATION>.
