<HEAD>Lorenzo, In Interview, Sticks By His Guns on Eastern</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARCY GORDON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. Chairman <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> remained locked on a collision course with the federal judge overseeing <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>' bankruptcy case by insisting Wednesday that the strike-wracked carrier will be shrunk not sold `` There are a lot of people out there who want to buy <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> for some beads, jelly beans or whatever comes to mind,'' <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> told a small group of reporters at <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> office. `` Eastern has to be built back the old-fashioned way ... We do n't think that any sale transaction makes sense.'' That position puts <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> at loggerheads with <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Bankruptcy Judge <PERSON> Burton </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Lifland </PERSON>, who appears poised to put the entire airline up for sale _ including assets held by Miami-based <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> before <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> acquired it three years ago for about $ 676 million. <PERSON> Lifland </PERSON>, who generally refrains from speaking to reporters on pending cases, was unavailable for comment. Furthermore, the 15-member committee representing <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s major creditors could be skeptical of <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON>'s plan to reduce <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> to 60 percent of its pre-strike size, sources said The committee is scheduled to meet Thursday, but <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> attorney <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Boies </PERSON> said the plan wo n't be presented to creditors until next week. <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERS