 the emotional aspect, I feel much more comfortable'' after a year on the job, <PERSON> Allen </PERSON> told a news conference. `` I have a good sense of the business, the people, what's important, where we're going.'' In long-distance, <PERSON> Allen </PERSON> said aggressive advertising and sales promotions, an expanded sales force and increased regulatory flexibility were paying off. Product sales grew 4.5 percent, mainly because of higher international sales of telecommunications network equipment and increases in microelectronic components, sales to the federal government and some computer products. Also, sales of the newly acquired <ORGANIZATION> Paradyne </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> were included in the results for the first time. Shareholders rejected a proposal by the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION>, a white-supremacist organization, to phase out aspects of <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T's affirmative action program `` which are directed toward recruiting, employing or promoting individuals from any particular racial or ethnic group. However, 8.1 percent of the shares were voted in favor, entitling the group to resubmit it next year. A proposal by an <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T employee, <PERSON> Alex </PERSON> <PERSON> Tillman </PERSON>, to strengthen and provide details on the affirmative action received support from 4.7 percent of the shares, falling below the 6 percent cutoff for resubmission. <PERSON> Allen </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T management opposed both proposals but reserved his main criticism for the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION> one, which he described as an insult to <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T employees.
