<HEAD>Bergner Sweetens Deal For Department Store Chain Carson Pirie</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 P.A. <ORGANIZATION> Bergner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, rebuffed last week in a takeover bid for <ORGANIZATION> Carson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pirie </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Scott </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, sweetened the deal Wednesday by offering $ 24 per share for the Chicago-based retailer. `` We remain convinced that a business combination involving your department stores and those of <PERSON> Bergner </PERSON>'s represents a sound business fit,'' <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON>, chairman of P.A. <PERSON> Bergner </PERSON>, said in a letter to <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> <PERSON> Pirie </PERSON>. <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> <PERSON> Pirie </PERSON>, which owns 33 department stores in <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION>, last week rejected a $ 20-per-share offer from P.A. <PERSON> Bergner </PERSON>, a Swiss-owned department store chain with headquarters in <LOCATION> Milwaukee </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> <PERSON> Pirie </PERSON> stock jumped by $ 1.62 -LCB- to close at $ 23.37 -LCB- Wednesday in consolidated <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> trading. `` We are prepared to pay $ 24 net in cash for each outstanding share of <PERSON> Carson </PERSON>'s common stock,'' <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON> wrote. `` This price represents an extraordinary premium over the recent trading history of <PERSON> Carson </PERSON>'s common stock.'' <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON> said the offer expires April 28. <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> <PERSON> Pirie </PERSON> issued a statement saying its directors `` would review the proposal ... in due course.'' In a letter to <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> <PERSON> Pirie </PERSON> directors, <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON> said he enclosed a copy of a letter from <ORGANIZATION> Swiss </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> confirming the bank would provide P.A. <PERSON> Bergner </PERSON> with the money necessary to acquire the outstanding shares and to refinance <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> <PERSON> Pirie </PERSON>'s debt. P.A. <PERSON> Bergner </PERSON> operates 31 department stores in <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> <PERSON> Pirie </PERSON> lost $ 38.8 million in the fiscal year that ended Jan. 31, much of it from its catalog operations. Besides department stores, <PERSON> Carson </PERSON> <PERSON> Pirie </PERSON> owns 388 County Seat speciality stores in <LOCATION> Midwest </LOCATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Sunbelt </ORGANIZATION> states and 23 <ORGANIZATION> Arcadia </ORGANIZATION> stores in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>.
