<HEAD>Motorola Seeks Halt Of Phone Sales In Patent Dispute</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: INSERTS 2 grafs after 8th graf pvs, `Named as ...,' to UPDATE
with Tandy comment and attempt to reach Nokia; Picks up last graf pvs.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SCHAUMBURG, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, citing patent violations, has filed complaints with the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> and in federal court to stop sales of some portable and mobile cellular telephones, the company said Wednesday. `` We expect our competition to respect <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION>'s hard-won patent position,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> Vice President <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> N. </PERSON> <PERSON> Weisshappel </PERSON>. He said talks with <ORGANIZATION> Nokia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Finland </LOCATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Tandy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mobira </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> had been fruitless. The infringements allow competitors to sell products at unfairly low prices, resulting in substantial injury to <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> and the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> cellular telephone industry, <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> said. <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> seeks permanent relief from the <ORGANIZATION> ITC </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, as well as a temporary exclusion order and a temporary cease-and-desist order to halt imports of cellular telephones, primarily from <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>, that it says infringe upon seven of its patents. In the court action, filed in <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> seeks a permanent injunction and unspecified monetary damages, citing infringement on nine patents. Named in the <ORGANIZATION> ITC </ORGANIZATION> action are <ORGANIZATION> Nokia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Helsinki </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Finland </LOCATION>; Nokia-Mobira Oy of <PERSON> Salo </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Finland </LOCATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Nokia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Basking </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ridge </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Nokia-Mobira </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Largo </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Tandy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mobira </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Tandy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>; and A & amp; A International of <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>. Named as defendants in the court action are <ORGANIZATION> Nokia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Nokia-Mobira </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Tandy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mobira </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Tandy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> `` We have n't seen the exact complaints,'' <ORGANIZATION> Tandy </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> Juge </PERSON> said. `` We've been talking to them through legal counsel for several months. Without knowing exactly what's involved, it's impossible to give relevant comment. A phone call placed to <ORGANIZATION> Nokia </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> operation after office hours Wednesday went unanswered. <ORGANIZATION> Motorola </ORGANIZATION> is one of the world's leading manufacturers of electronics equipment, systems and components for world markets. Its products include two-way radios, pagers, cellular telephone systems, defense and aerospace electronics, and information processing and handling equipment.
